titlestmt.titleproper: A Guide to the American Conservation Association (ACA) records FA475

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2024-11-01 04:09:16 UTC.

physdesc.extent: 218 letter size document boxes, 1 legal size document box, 2 oversized flat boxes, 1 small artifact box

processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: Preliminary archival processing of the records was conducted by the Rockefeller Archive Center to establish intellectual and physical control of the material and assess its immediate preservation and conservation needs. The collection remains in storage boxes and original folders. Further archival processing, primarily to arrange the records to facilitate more efficient access to the collection and address its long-term preservation, will be conducted at a later date, as necessary.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Archival Materials note
relatedmaterial.p: Island Resources Foundation records Jackson Hole Preserve, Inc. records Laurance S. Rockefeller papers Willam H. Whyte papers

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 15 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The collection primarily consists of grant files, administrative records and financial records.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged as received by Rockefeller Archive Center.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition note
acqinfo.p: American Conservation Association deposited the records at the Rockefeller Archive Center in April 1985.
RAC began receiving ACA records in 1990 (Accession 1990:117). Additions and accruals to the collection have been received in multiple accessions, and continue periodically as applicable.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: American Conservation Association retains title, copyright and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them. Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.
